Number of records with zero values in each column -¶

Glucose 5¶

BloodPressure 34¶

SkinThickness 220¶

Insulin 366¶

BMI 10¶

DiabetesPedigreeFunction 0¶

Age 0¶

Looks like there are no zero values in the Age and DiabetesPedigreeFunction.¶

Highest number of zeros are in Insulin(366 records) followed by¶

Skinthickness(220 records)¶

Easyiest way to handle these zero value records is we can delete them but we¶

loose huge portion of the records in the dataset and Also, we can not provide¶

valubale insights from the remaining data.¶

Best possible way to handle the zeros values without losing the data is replacing¶

them with the Mean or Median values of the same field.¶

In [200]:
#Replace all columns with zero values by it's meadian and mean values.

pd.options.mode.chained_assignment = None
Pima_diabetes1['Glucose'] = Pima_diabetes1['Glucose'].map( lambda x : Pima_diabetes1.Glucose.median() if x == 0 else x)
Pima_diabetes1['BloodPressure'] = Pima_diabetes1['BloodPressure'].map( lambda x : Pima_diabetes1.BloodPressure.median() if x == 0 else x)
Pima_diabetes1['SkinThickness'] = Pima_diabetes1['SkinThickness'].map( lambda x : Pima_diabetes1.SkinThickness.median() if x == 0 else x)
Pima_diabetes1['Insulin'] = Pima_diabetes1['Insulin'].map( lambda x : Pima_diabetes1.Insulin.mean() if x == 0 else x)
Pima_diabetes1['BMI'] = Pima_diabetes1['BMI'].map( lambda x : Pima_diabetes1.BMI.median() if x == 0 else x)

#Create Age buckets after resetting the index.

Pima_diabetes4.reset_index(inplace=True)
bins = pd.Series([])
for i in Pima_diabetes4.index:
    if (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 25).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["20-25"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 30).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["26-30"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 35).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["31-35"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 40).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["36-40"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 45).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["41-45"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 50).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["46-50"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 55).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["51-55"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 60).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["56-60"]))
    elif (Pima_diabetes4.loc[i:i,]["Age"] <= 65).bool(): bins = bins.append(pd.Series(["61-65"]))
    else: bins = bins.append(pd.Series([">65"]))
bins.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
Pima_diabetes4["Ages"] = bins
Pima_diabetes4.head()
